                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a press conference on October 8, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ADG1"
                        >Acheson</persName> stated that the duration of the recess was up to the
                    Communists and that the United Nations Command was prepared to meet with the
                    opposing delegates at Panmunjom when the Communists were ready to accept any of
                    the United Nations’ numerous proposals or when they made a constructive proposal
                    of their own. For the text of <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName>’s
                    statement, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 20,
                    1952, page 600.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
